description:
Learn how God's design measures days from evening to evening, establishing the framework for understanding the Sabbath. Delve into the clarity provided by Mark in defining 'evening' and discover the scriptural basis in Leviticus 23:32 for celebrating the Sabbath from sunset to sunset. Uncover the importance of recognizing Friday sunset as the beginning of the Sabbath, aligning with the Genesis narrative that defines a day with the sequence of evening and morning.
